messages.text: I was just about to text you. Are you okay?
Sorry I tried to break-up with you.
Are you out of Houston yet?
Me and about a billion other people who just went through processing…
are now crammed in a building…
waiting to go down to the transports.
I heard it’s getting hairy there.
I thought what I saw yesterday was crazy, but this…
And there’s a line of tanks stretching for miles
along the east side of the city.
Literally thousands of them just sitting there.
maybe two hundred thousand of them…
Sweeping through the towns west of Houston.
You can literally see it moving like a human tidal wave.
They just run until something gets in their way.
Then they either go over it or through it…
The ones they kill get up and move with the others.
No wonder so many were beyond the blast zone yesterday.
Who the hell is filming this?
CNN sent some lunatic reporters with troops in Apache helicopters.
They're gunning them down by the hundreds…
but most get back up and keep going.
Like someone turned on a faucet over central Texas.
They’re flooding out in every direction.
The floodlights on the tanks down below us…
And I can see the wave coming.
The tanks are firing on them. But they keep coming.
Why haven’t they moved you yet?
Shit, people in here are starting to panic.
God dammit! Why aren’t they getting you out of there?!
I mean why aren’t they getting YOU out?!
Some of them have reached the barbed wire just past the tanks.
They’re literally being shredded by machine guns.
Christ, why do they keep coming?!
Don’t they know who you are?!!
OK. I’m on my way out.
Can’t type and walk so keep texting to me news.
It’s bad. You need to get out of there.
They’re overrunning the tanks and pouring into the city.
I’m on the transport, now. I’m okay.
One of the Apaches got too close to a building..
Those things swarmed all over it…
it’s going down into the city!
Jesus it’s right in front of us!
It went over us and crashed into a building.
The entire city, east of the military zone…
so they don’t accidentally set off the charges in the buildings.
My transport is first in the convoy…
and we’re fucking flying through the city now.
and those things are still coming fast…
Can’t it wait until you’re safe?
Do you believe my dad started this?
You know he wouldn’t do this.
and he said Woody wasn’t the guy we thought he was.
No one willing to kill half the planet…
Would turn around and destroy the country…
if he was gonna kill billions…
There was something wrong with him…
But I’m sure I’ll know the truth when I look in his eyes.
No, your dad promised to take me to see him.
Getting on I-10. Leaving the city.
I wish this fucker would slow down.
Those were the charges going off in the buildings.
set off in hundreds of buildings across the city.
To kill as many of those things as possible…
And to create a rubble pile that will hopefully keep them from following the transports.
They just took the city of Houston off the fucking map.
Dad said we reached a tipping point.
Yeah, he said something like that to me, too.
I know this isn’t the time…
Was something going on between your dad and my mom?
He seems hell bent on finding me and keeping me close.
He said it’s because he promised mom he would protect me…
But he promised me the same thing.
So there’s nothing special about me...
No, I mean to the military.
(But thanks for saying the other stuff, BTW). ☺
I don’t know of any reason for them to want you.
Not that I’m privy to that sort of thing.
slammed a car on the side of the highway.
I knew he was going too fast.
But the others are catching up now.
Get on one and get out of there before the infected get there.
THEY’RE BLOWING UP THE BRIDGES ONCE THE TRANSPORTS ARE ACROSS!
But I see them and there’s no getting away.
No one left here is surviving this.
So I’m not wasting my last seconds running.
I’m using them to tell you
I’m sorry, Christian, but they’re here.
